**As I was leaving home to go to college, I felt that someone was following me. Today, I could not see any rickshaws on the road. Since I was already late for college, I decided to walk. It was an early winter morning and the streets were dark and empty with no cars in sight. I could still feel that I was being followed. When I turned around there was no one I could see; however, I started to feel scared. The streets were empty and the shops were closed. It felt like there was a curfew. I increased my speed, it was as if I was running and yet it felt pointless as the college was still two kilometers away. It was then, suddenly, he appeared in front of me, a hefty, tall, bearded, and black cloak clad Tantric. He had a necklace strung with skulls with a Trishul in hand and big red eyes. I was numb with fear as his big red eyes just kept staring at me. The "eleventh sutra" he whispered. In an instant, he threw me over his shoulder and started to run. I was being kidnapped in broad daylight! I wanted to scream but my throat was choked out of fear. Finally, when I did manage to let out a scream for help, I found myself awake, on my bed with my sheets drenched in sweat.** - <@1053730420862234634> (fast)
